s from the equatorial plane. This suggests\nthat the traditional classification of global magnetic fields has difficulty\nreproducing the global structure of the magnetic fields. Finally, we\ndemonstrate the method to separate magnetic flux tubes at different heights by\nusing peak frequencies which cause the decreasing of polarized flux.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 5 Mar 2023 15:43:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-07"}
